# 🏢 Lab 09 - Small Office Network Simulation

## 📌 Overview
This project simulates a small office network using Cisco Packet Tracer.  
It demonstrates LAN connectivity, wireless networking, DHCP, and device communication in a real office scenario.

---

## 🖥️ Network Components
- Cisco Router (1841)
- Switch
- Wireless Router (Access Point Mode)
- HR Laptop
- Staff Laptop
- HR Mobile (WiFi Client)
- Network Printer

---

## 🌐 IP Addressing Scheme
- Network: `192.168.0.0/24`
- Default Gateway: `192.168.0.1`
- Wireless Router: `192.168.0.2`
- Printer: `192.168.0.12`
- HR Laptop: `192.168.0.10`
- Staff Laptop: `192.168.0.11`
- Smartphone: DHCP Assigned

---

## ⚙️ Key Configurations
- LAN setup using Switch
- Wireless network (SSID configured)
- DHCP enabled for automatic IP assignment
- Static IPs for critical devices
- Wired and wireless integration

---

## 🧪 Testing Results
- Ping between devices successful ✔️  
- Wireless connection established ✔️  
- Device-to-device communication verified ✔️  
- Printer connectivity confirmed via network ✔️  

